00:04:55,360 --> 00:05:01,660
Timing components are a resistor and capacitor on the Schmitt trigger input.

76
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:03,620
How does this work?

77
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:17,220
The signal from TL goes through 10 Ω resistors, reaches the input, gets inverted and exits to the resistor.

78
00:05:18,940 --> 00:05:33,120
The resistor is a current-limiting element in the system, so it regulates the number of charges passing per unit time through the conductor's cross-section and through this resistance.

79
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:39,160
And accordingly it regulates the charging time of this capacitance.

80
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:47,260
That is, we understand higher resistance, the capacitance charges longer and we get this interesting effect.

81
00:05:48,180 --> 00:05:51,520
Now I'll present it, if we look.

82
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:58,880
On the capacitance we have an edge slope, that is, the moment of charging, voltage rise is sloped.

83
00:05:59,540 --> 00:06:09,360
And the trigger has a hysteresis point, that is, the trigger moment when it switches from zero position to one.

84
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:15,520
So, the longer this slope moment, the later the trigger will switch.

85
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:26,470
And consequently this way we can on this point, playing with it, adjusting the resistance, we can set the moment when our trigger will switch with delay.

86
00:06:28,780 --> 00:06:36,740
We do this so it's convenient for us later to control the Tesla and work with anticipation.

87
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:43,740
That is, so we can move across the entire width of the current sine wave.

88
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:54,540
If we don't make this delay, our signal will lag in time, and we'll constantly hit the wrong zone, where the current sine is falling.

89
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,380
And basically there's nothing to do there.

90
00:06:57,200 --> 00:07:03,240
Striking at a falling magnetic field, at a decaying current, has absolutely no sense.

91
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:10,800
Even less sense to hammer in dead time, as we have such misinformation on the internet.

92
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:16,380
In dead time the current is in zero in general, so you can't ramp up absolutely anything there.

